The paper deals with approximation algorithms for optimization problems on graphs and hypergraphs, which are central topics in computer science. The use of ear-decompositions and forest representations suggests a connection to data structures (cs.DS) and computational geometry (cs.CG). The study of approximation algorithms and LP relaxations is a common theme in discrete mathematics (cs.DM) and theoretical computer science (cs.CC). Finally, the focus on graph connectivity and spanning subgraphs suggests a connection to graph theory (cs.GT).
